merb_relaxdb
============

A plugin for the Merb framework that provides integration with CouchDB via the RelaxDB gem.

merb_relaxdb expects your merb app to augment the standard layout as listed in tree below.
couchdb.yml is mandatory. Reference data, sample data and views are optional.
couchdb.yml.sample is supplied in this distribution. Copy and modify as necessary.

To use merb_relaxdb, list 'dependency "merb_relaxdb"' in in the dependency section of your_merb_app/config/init.rb, but not in the Merb::BootLoader.after_app_loads block.

For more details on using RelaxDB, see the RelaxDB readme and specs.

my_merb_app $ tree
.
|-- Rakefile
|-- app
|-- autotest
|-- config
|   |-- couchdb.yml
|-- couchdb
|   |-- data
|   |   |-- reference
|   |   |   `-- reference_data.rb
|   |   `-- sample
|   |       `-- sample_data.rb
|   `-- views
|       `-- views.js
|-- lib
|-- log
|-- public
|-- scratch
`-- spec
